<exercise checkit-seed="0001" checkit-slug="G1" checkit-title="Row operations and determinants">
  <statement>
      <p>Let <m>A</m> be a <m>4 \times 4</m> matrix with determinant <m>-4</m>.</p>
      <ol>
          <li>Let <m>P</m> be the matrix obtained from <m>A</m> by applying the row operation <m>R_4 \to -5R_4</m>.
              What is <m>\operatorname{det}\ P</m>?</li>
          <li>Let <m>M</m> be the matrix obtained from <m>A</m> by applying the row operation <m>R_3 \to R_3 + -4R_2</m>.
              What is <m>\operatorname{det}\ M</m>?</li>
          <li>Let <m>N</m> be the matrix obtained from <m>A</m> by applying the row operation <m>R_3 \leftrightarrow R_4</m>.
              What is <m>\operatorname{det}\ N</m>?</li>
      </ol>
  </statement>
  <answer>
       <ol>
          <li><m>\operatorname{det}\ P=20</m></li>
          <li><m>\operatorname{det}\ M=-4</m></li>
          <li><m>\operatorname{det}\ N=4</m></li>
      </ol>
  </answer>
</exercise>
